{
  "texts": [
    "Observe the close analogy to more traditional definitions of the term \"agents:\" In computer science and robotics, agents have traditionally been described as entities that perceive their environment via sensors and act on it via actuators.",
    "In our example, these sensors and actuators are given by external tools that the reasoning engine can call upon.",
    "In economics, agents maximize an objective subject to information and resource constraints.",
    "In our example, AI agents seek to fulfill the objective given by the initial prompt.",
    "They operate within token and memory limits and subject to the tools they have access."
  ]
}